Phase 1 â€“ Foundation

Goal: understand Djangoâ€™s structure, ORM, and migrations.

Create your project manually:

django-admin startproject gedcomx_project
cd gedcomx_project
python manage.py startapp core


In core.models, hand-write:

BaseModel (with uri, timestamps)

A URIField using Django validators or rfc3986

A test Person table with name

Run:

python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser
python manage.py runserver


Explore the admin to see what migrations actually produce in your DB.

ðŸ§± Phase 2 â€“ Relational modeling

Goal: see how foreign keys and many-to-manys work.

Add a separate places app with PlaceDescription and PlaceResolution.

Create FK links manually.

Observe migration dependencies between apps.

Add a Fact model in persons with a place FK and test how cascading deletes behave.

Use the Django shell (python manage.py shell_plus) to experiment with:

p = Person.objects.create(uri="http://example.org/person/1", primary_name="John Doe")
f = Fact.objects.create(person=p, type_uri="http://gedcomx.org/Birth")

